## Auto-update from GitHub

- **Production client** checks the GitHub repo’s **latest full release** (tag `vX.Y.Z`).
- **Staging client** ("PBooks Pro Client (Staging)") checks **prereleases** only — it will not pick up production releases.
- **API Server (Staging)** uses update channel `api-server-staging`; production API Server uses channel `api-server`.
- Set `GH_TOKEN` or `GITHUB_TOKEN` in `.env.staging` / `.env.production` (repo scope). Without a token, builds still run locally but nothing is uploaded to GitHub.

